headline: EL Q2 Deep Dive: Underlying Consumer and Channel Shifts Shape Outlook Amid Margin Pressures
summary: Beauty products company Estée Lauder (NYSE:EL) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, but sales fell by 12% year on year to $3.41 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.09 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.
